<br>
But snaring someone and using it is pretty cheap in my opinion, especially a caster.  They have to eat the entire discipline that way.  It's a lot more honorable to hotkey it and try to work it into a driveby in my opinion.<br>
<br>
Paladins own the high end of the game, when it comes to dueling.  Relix of Tunare can take on entire groups by himself, without even getting hurt or out of mana.  On the server-wide FFA, an entire guild targeted Relix and Relix alone, because no one's ever been able to kill him before, and well.. they wanted the honor.<br>
<br>
Sure enough, after solo'ing half the guild(the other half pretty much got taken apart by the crowd), he finished the rest of the arena off and walked away the victor.<br>
<br>
As a Rogue fighting him, I can do an insane amount of damage, and have him still be at full HP at the end, without him even casting a spell -during- the fight.  I mean c'mon, the guys a hybrid that can backhand pure melees, with nothing but melee.<br>
<br>
